Back in the car, you grin. "The man was very helpful."

"Would that he had snooped further in his employer's private affairs."

"It's a good quality to have. I'm sure he appreciated his EA's discretion."

"Oh," scoffs your wife, "I think perhaps his spirit would prefer that his murderer see justice."

"Well, he always struck me as a worldly guy. I think he might be an atheist, actually."

"Really? More fool him. His spirit won't appreciate that at all."

